{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B8T1ZA7fRddRAxuTsiJS2t","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Pyth Network BTC/USD feed ID hex price feed identifiers\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Price Feeds | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"BTC/USD | Pyth Network Insights\",\"url\":\"https://insights.pyth.network/price-feeds/Crypto.BTC%2FUSD\"},{\"title\":\"Price Feed IDs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/pro/price-feed-ids\"},{\"title\":\"The Price of Everything | Pyth Network\",\"url\":\"https://www.pyth.network/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"Fetch Price Updates | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/fetch-price-updates\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - elizaos-plugins/plugin-pyth-data: Integrates with Pyth Network for real-time price feeds and data streams across multiple asset classes.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/elizaos-plugins/plugin-pyth-data\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth Price Feed IDs | Dune\",\"url\":\"https://dune.com/queries/3874479\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth Network price today, PYTH to USD live price, marketcap and chart | CoinMarketCap\",\"url\":\"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/pyth-network/\"},{\"title\":\"Oracles | Movement Docs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.movementnetwork.xyz/devs/oracles\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found the Pyth Network BTC/USD feed ID in hexadecimal format:\n\nThe BTC/USD price feed ID is `0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43`.\n\nPrice Feed IDs are unique identifiers for each specific pair of assets being priced (e.g. BTC/USD), and every price update is tagged with the corresponding price feed ID.\n\nThis hex identifier can be used when calling Pyth Network APIs to fetch price updates for Bitcoin in US dollars. For a complete list of all available price feed IDs across different asset classes, you can refer to the official Pyth documentation at https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/price-feeds.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"58187759-7f39-424b-a709-e191aa875d58"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F65R6odd6LsmpUKK9mqYFX","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"PriceUpdateV2 account layout bytes offset solana pyth-solana-receiver-sdk\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-crosschain/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk/src/price_update.rs at main · pyth-network/pyth-crosschain\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-crosschain/blob/main/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk/src/price_update.rs\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-solana-receiver-sdk - crates.io: Rust Package Registry\",\"url\":\"https://crates.io/crates/pyth-solana-receiver-sdk\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-crosschain/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk at main · pyth-network/pyth-crosschain\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-crosschain/tree/main/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - mithraiclabs/pyth-min: A minimal no-dependency sdk for interacting with Pyth oracles on Solana\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/mithraiclabs/pyth-min\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth: How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Developers | Eclipse Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.eclipse.xyz/developers/tutorials-and-guides/developer-guides/pyth-how-to-use-real-time-data-in-solana-programs\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-crosschain/target_chains/solana/sdk/js/pyth_solana_receiver at main · pyth-network/pyth-crosschain\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-crosschain/tree/main/target_chains/solana/sdk/js/pyth_solana_receiver\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - rain-foundation/pyth-solana-receiver-sdk\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/rain-foundation/pyth-solana-receiver-sdk\"},{\"title\":\"Troubleshoot Solana Price Feeds Contract | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/troubleshoot/svm\"},{\"title\":\"@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver\"}]\n\nI found search results related to the Pyth Solana Receiver SDK and PriceUpdateV2 accounts. Here's what I found:\n\nPriceUpdateV2 guarantees that the account contains a verified price for some price feed at some point in time. For developers using Anchor, you can simply add an Account<'info, PriceUpdateV2> field to the Context struct.\n\nThe search results show that you can borrow the account data minus the 8-byte Anchor discriminator and then use `PriceUpdateV2::get_price_update_v2_from_bytes(data)` to parse the price data.\n\nHowever, the search results don't contain specific information about the detailed account layout byte offsets for PriceUpdateV2. For more detailed information about the exact byte offset structure of the PriceUpdateV2 account layout, you may need to:\n\n1. Check the source code directly in the [pyth-solana-receiver-sdk repository](https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-crosschain/blob/main/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk/src/price_update.rs)\n2. Review the Rust struct definition in the SDK's source code\n3. Consult the Pyth documentation or SDK documentation for detailed binary format specifications\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about the account layout structure?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"68f60280-dc0e-4108-abd6-3a806b9658cb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DAU3p2vbGkdwXKfhmwcR8C","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Pyth Network Solana devnet BTC/USD price account address push oracle PriceUpdateV2\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to Use Pyth for Price Feeds on Solana | Quicknode Guides\",\"url\":\"https://www.quicknode.com/guides/solana-development/3rd-party-integrations/pyth-price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth: How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Developers | Eclipse Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.eclipse.xyz/developers/tutorials-and-guides/developer-guides/pyth-how-to-use-real-time-data-in-solana-programs\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-sdk-solana 0.10.6 - Docs.rs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.rs/crate/pyth-sdk-solana/latest\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth Pull Oracle Launches on Solana - Blog - Pyth Network\",\"url\":\"https://www.pyth.network/blog/pyth-network-pull-oracle-on-solana\"},{\"title\":\"Push Integration | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/push-integration\"},{\"title\":\"on Solana | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/push-feeds/solana\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-sdk-solana - crates.io: Rust Package Registry\",\"url\":\"https://crates.io/crates/pyth-sdk-solana/0.2.0\"},{\"title\":\"The Price Layer for Global Finance | Pyth Network\",\"url\":\"https://www.pyth.network/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyth-network/pyth-client-rs: Rust client for pyth on-chain data\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-client-rs\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about Pyth Network's integration with Solana devnet. Here are the key findings:\n\n## BTC/USD Account Address on Solana Devnet\n\nFor Solana devnet, the BTC/USD price feed account address is HovQMDrbAgAYPCmHVSrezcSmkMtXSSUsLDFANExrZh2J.\n\n## PriceUpdateV2 and Push/Pull Oracle\n\nUsing Anchor with the Account<'info, PriceUpdateV2> type will automatically perform account ownership checks, which is important for ensuring the account is owned by the Pyth oracle program.\n\nPrice feed accounts hold a sequence of prices for a specific price feed ID and have a fixed address that your program can depend on, with the Pyth Data Association maintaining a set of price feed accounts that are continuously updated.\n\n## Oracle Types\n\nThe Pyth Network offers two oracle models:\n- The push oracle design receives price inputs from data providers via Solana transactions and generates price aggregates directly, pushing these aggregate prices on-chain for every supported price feed\n- The pull oracle design, developed as Pythnet Price Feeds, only updates the on-chain price when requested, with the Pythnet appchain aggregating prices from data providers every slot\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"c6fd9e46-4296-4531-8886-caa74d7900e3"}
