{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018mobaMBjANyDWg43VdcZrT","type":"tool_result","content":"# Struct Definitions from price_update.rs\n\n## VerificationLevel\n```rust\npub enum VerificationLevel {\n    Partial {\n        num_signatures: u8,\n    },\n    Full,\n}\n```\n\n## PriceUpdateV2\n```rust\n#[account]\n#[derive(BorshSchema)]\npub struct PriceUpdateV2 {\n    pub write_authority: Pubkey,\n    pub verification_level: VerificationLevel,\n    pub price_message: PriceFeedMessage,\n    pub posted_slot: u64,\n}\n\nimpl PriceUpdateV2 {\n    pub const LEN: usize = 8 + 32 + 2 + 32 + 8 + 8 + 4 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8;\n}\n```\n\nThe `#[account]` attribute indicates this is an Anchor account with an 8-byte discriminator prepended.\n\n## PriceFeedMessage\nThe file imports this type: `pub use pythnet_sdk::messages::{FeedId, PriceFeedMessage};`\n\nBased on usage in tests, PriceFeedMessage contains:\n- `feed_id: [u8; 32]`\n- `price: i64`\n- `conf: u64`\n- `exponent: i32`\n- `publish_time: i64`\n- `prev_publish_time: i64`\n- `ema_price: i64`\n- `ema_conf: u64`\n\n## Binary Layout Summary\n**PriceUpdateV2 total size**: 152 bytes (including 8-byte discriminator)\n- Discriminator: 8 bytes\n- write_authority (Pubkey): 32 bytes\n- verification_level: 2 bytes\n- price_message (PriceFeedMessage): ~100 bytes\n- posted_slot (u64): 8 bytes"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"779b2db1-d698-4c9f-88f6-b8f029634ccc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015EeFKyjebZjpXgTz15NcbH","type":"tool_result","content":"# Pyth Price Feed Information\n\n## BTC/USD Price Feed ID\n\nThe page content provided does not explicitly list the BTC/USD price feed ID in hex format. The document references that \"Price Feed IDs are unique identifiers for each specific pair of assets being priced (e.g. BTC/USD)\" and directs users to the [Price Feed IDs page](https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/price-feeds/price-feed-ids) for the complete list, but the actual ID values are not included in this excerpt.\n\n## Solana Price Feed Accounts\n\nAccording to the documentation: \"On Solana, each feed additionally has a collection of **price feed accounts** containing the feed's data. The addresses of these accounts are programmatically derived from the feed id and a shard id, which is simply a 16-bit number.\"\n\nThe page references a separate guide for detailed information: \"See [How to Use Real-Time Data on Solana](../use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana#price-feed-accounts) for more information on price feed accounts.\"\n\n## Solana Devnet Details\n\nThe provided content does not contain specific Solana devnet account addresses or program IDs. To obtain this information, you would need to consult the linked Solana integration guide or the [Contract Addresses documentation](https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/contract-addresses/solana) for SVM networks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"838e7fff-f332-4320-9498-a056cbcdfa6d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017UsvhPqqUwwZsMD8W21p9S","type":"tool_result","content":"# Pyth Push Oracle Information on Solana\n\nBased on the provided web page content, I can only offer limited information, as the page appears to be a navigation/index page rather than detailed documentation.\n\n## What's Available\n\nThe page shows this is documentation for **\"Push Feeds on Solana\"** with a table listing various price feeds including SOL/USD, BTC/USD, ETH/USD, and others. However, the specific details you're requesting are not included in this excerpt.\n\n## Information Not Found\n\n1. **Program ID for Pyth push oracle on devnet** - Not provided in this content\n2. **BTC/USD price account address on devnet** - Not provided in this content\n3. **Account format/layout details** - Not included in this excerpt\n4. **Differences between push feed and PriceUpdateV2 accounts** - Not discussed\n\n## What IS Shown\n\nThe table indicates that push feeds have associated account addresses (shown as truncated values like \"4cSM2e...PSPo\" for BTC/USD) and price feed IDs (like \"e62df6...5b43\"), but complete addresses are abbreviated in this view.\n\n## Recommendation\n\nTo find the specific technical details you need, you would likely need to access the actual push feeds documentation page directly or consult the Pyth developer documentation's contract addresses or reference material sections."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"3bd17c77-791e-403e-9d88-e54923030c75"}
