{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Krx8aZmUm7QmNcQ4MvHK1v","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Pyth push oracle Solana devnet BTC/USD price feed account address \"4cSM2e\" OR \"HovQMDrbAg\"\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to Use Pyth for Price Feeds on Solana | Quicknode Guides\",\"url\":\"https://www.quicknode.com/guides/solana-development/3rd-party-integrations/pyth-price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"Price Feeds | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"on Solana | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/push-feeds/solana\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-sdk-solana 0.10.6 - Docs.rs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.rs/crate/pyth-sdk-solana/latest\"},{\"title\":\"@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth: How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Developers | Eclipse Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.eclipse.xyz/developers/tutorials-and-guides/developer-guides/pyth-how-to-use-real-time-data-in-solana-programs\"},{\"title\":\"Push Integration | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/push-integration\"},{\"title\":\"The Price of Everything | Pyth Network\",\"url\":\"https://www.pyth.network/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyth-network/pyth-client-rs: Rust client for pyth on-chain data\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-client-rs\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found the information you were looking for:\n\nFor the Solana devnet BTC/USD price feed on Pyth, the account address is HovQMDrbAgAYPCmHVSrezcSmkMtXSSUsLDFANExrZh2J.\n\nThis address (\"HovQMDrbAg\") matches one of the account address fragments you specified in your query. This is the primary price feed account address used for accessing BTC/USD pricing data on Solana's devnet network through the Pyth oracle.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"777fb224-ed2d-42b3-804b-da7ec405424b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fruhc4QGXWVKkfUPz2qeDM","type":"tool_result","content":"# Pyth Oracle Program IDs on Solana/SVM\n\nBased on the documentation provided, here are the key program addresses:\n\n## Main Oracle Programs\n\n**Price Feed Program** (used across all Solana/SVM networks):\n- Address: `pythWSnswVUd12oZpeFP8e9CVaEqJg25g1Vtc2biRsT`\n- Deployed on: Solana Mainnet, Devnet, Eclipse, Sonic, Atlas, and Fogo networks\n\n**Solana Receiver Program** (for cross-chain price updates):\n- Address: `rec5EKMGg6MxZYaMdyBfgwp4d5rB9T1VQH5pJv5LtFJ`\n- Also deployed consistently across all supported SVM chains\n\n## Key Distinction\n\nThe documentation states: \"The Pyth Oracle consists of two different programs.\" The receiver program handles incoming price data from cross-chain sources, while the price feed program manages the actual price information accessible to smart contracts and programs.\n\n## Important Note\n\nThe provided content does not include specific individual price feed account addresses for BTC/USD or other assets. The documentation references \"Price Feeds\" as a reference section but the actual feed IDs and their corresponding account addresses are not detailed in this excerpt. Users would need to consult additional resources or the Price Feed IDs documentation for specific asset account addresses."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"95a4b381-f894-4ff9-a672-6db2dfcff6d4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016L5obTzB69gNwTGSjVx7Rd","type":"tool_result","content":"# Struct Definitions and Binary Layout\n\n## VerificationLevel\n```rust\npub enum VerificationLevel {\n    Partial { num_signatures: u8 },  // 1 byte + 1 byte padding\n    Full,                             // 1 byte + 7 bytes padding\n}\n```\n**Size**: 8 bytes (with discriminator in serialization)\n\n## PriceUpdateV2\n```rust\npub struct PriceUpdateV2 {\n    pub write_authority: Pubkey,           // 32 bytes\n    pub verification_level: VerificationLevel, // 8 bytes\n    pub price_message: PriceFeedMessage,   // 32 bytes (feed_id only shown)\n    pub posted_slot: u64,                  // 8 bytes\n}\n```\n\n**Declared LEN constant**: `8 + 32 + 2 + 32 + 8 + 8 + 4 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 = 136 bytes`\n\nThis includes:\n- 8 bytes: Anchor discriminator\n- 32 bytes: write_authority\n- Variable fields totaling ~96 bytes for verification_level and price_message components\n\n## PriceFeedMessage\nNot fully defined in the provided content (imported from `pythnet_sdk`), but based on usage in tests, it contains:\n- `feed_id: [u8; 32]`\n- `price: i64`\n- `conf: u64`\n- `exponent: i32`\n- `publish_time: i64`\n- Additional fields: `ema_conf`, `ema_price`, `prev_publish_time`\n\nThe \"actual price is `(price ± conf)* 10^exponent`\" according to the documentation provided."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"008cb579-80bd-4050-88d8-d531449a043d"}
