{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NPJmnB7Yv2kA5yY86yd2F4","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Pyth push feeds solana \"pythWSnswVUd12oZpeFP8e9CVaEqJg25g1Vtc2biRsT\" price feed account PDA derivation shard_id\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Price Feeds | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"on Solana | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/push-feeds/solana\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Pyth for Price Feeds on Solana | Quicknode Guides\",\"url\":\"https://www.quicknode.com/guides/solana-development/3rd-party-integrations/pyth-price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver\"},{\"title\":\"Push Integration | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/push-integration\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth: How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Developers | Eclipse Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.eclipse.xyz/developers/tutorials-and-guides/developer-guides/pyth-how-to-use-real-time-data-in-solana-programs\"},{\"title\":\"on Solana/SVM | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/contract-addresses/solana\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-sdk-solana 0.10.6 - Docs.rs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.rs/crate/pyth-sdk-solana/latest\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-solana-receiver-sdk - crates.io: Rust Package Registry\",\"url\":\"https://crates.io/crates/pyth-solana-receiver-sdk\"}]\n\nI found relevant information about Pyth price feeds on Solana. Here are the key findings:\n\n## Price Feed Account PDA Derivation\n\nOn Solana, the addresses of price feed accounts are programmatically derived from the feed id and a shard id, which is simply a 16-bit number.\n\n## Shard ID Concept\n\nPrice feed accounts have a fixed address derived from the feed id and a shard id. The shard id allows different applications to use different accounts for the same feed, thereby reducing the impact of solana congestion.\n\nThere are up to 2^16 different accounts for any given price feed id.\n\n## Push Feeds on Solana\n\nDevelopers on Solana and related ecosystems can use price feed accounts to consume push feeds. See the Solana integration guide for implementation details.\n\n## Default Sponsored Feeds\n\nThe Pyth Data Association sponsors price updates for a subset of commonly used price feeds on shard 0.\n\nThe search results provide documentation about how Pyth push feeds work with shard_id-based PDA derivation on Solana, though the specific account address you mentioned (`pythWSnswVUd12oZpeFP8e9CVaEqJg25g1Vtc2biRsT`) would need to be looked up in the Pyth registry to identify which feed and shard it corresponds to.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"59ef34da-2f12-48ba-8464-b004b3d797f8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RjGDk8Yj8wXZYaMHVVWJRo","type":"tool_result","content":"# Push Integration on Solana: Key Information\n\nBased on the provided documentation, here's what I found regarding your specific questions:\n\n## 1. How Push Feeds Work on Solana\n\nThe guide states: \"Developers on Solana and related ecosystems can use price feed accounts to consume push feeds.\" However, **the page lacks detailed implementation instructions** for the SVM/Solana ecosystem. It references a separate Solana integration guide for specifics.\n\n## 2. Account Format of Push Feed Accounts\n\nThe documentation **does not specify the account structure** for Solana push feed accounts. It only directs readers to \"See the Solana integration guide\" without providing format details in this excerpt.\n\n## 3. PriceUpdateV2 Format Usage\n\n**No information is provided** about whether push feed accounts use PriceUpdateV2 format. This technical detail is not addressed in the Push Integration guide.\n\n## 4. BTC/USD Push Feed Account Address\n\nThe document does **not include specific account addresses**, including for BTC/USD. The EVM example shows: `0xff61491a931112ddf1bd8147cd1b641375f79f5825126d665480874634fd0ace` for ETH/USD, but no Solana equivalents are listed.\n\n## 5. Devnet-Specific Information\n\n**No devnet information is provided** in this guide. The page focuses only on mainnet implementations.\n\n## 6. Push Feeds vs. Receiver/Price Feed Program Relationship\n\nThis relationship is **not explained** in the provided content. The guide omits architectural details about program interactions on Solana.\n\n**Recommendation**: Consult the referenced Solana integration guide at `/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana` for complete implementation details."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"64ad779f-90d2-40ce-8895-d39d3e758979"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QwCQEGULNbp43kWXKdGNwf","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"pyth solana push oracle price feed account \"price_feed_account\" PDA seeds shard_id feed_id derivation\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"Price Feeds | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Pyth for Price Feeds on Solana | Quicknode Guides\",\"url\":\"https://www.quicknode.com/guides/solana-development/3rd-party-integrations/pyth-price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"on Solana | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/push-feeds/solana\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-sdk-solana 0.10.6 - Docs.rs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.rs/crate/pyth-sdk-solana/latest\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth: How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Developers | Eclipse Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.eclipse.xyz/developers/tutorials-and-guides/developer-guides/pyth-how-to-use-real-time-data-in-solana-programs\"},{\"title\":\"@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver\"},{\"title\":\"Push Integration | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/push-integration\"},{\"title\":\"Explaining kinds of price feed program / account - Price Feeds - Pyth Developer Forum\",\"url\":\"https://dev-forum.pyth.network/t/explaining-kinds-of-price-feed-program-account/138\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth Pull Oracle Launches on Solana - Blog - Pyth Network\",\"url\":\"https://www.pyth.network/blog/pyth-network-pull-oracle-on-solana\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I can provide you with information about Pyth price feed accounts on Solana:\n\n## Price Feed Account Derivation\n\nThe addresses of price feed accounts are programmatically derived from the feed id and a shard id, which is simply a 16-bit number.\n\n## Understanding Shard ID and Feed ID\n\nThere are up to 2^16 different accounts for any given price feed id. The shard id indicates which of these accounts you would like to use. However, you may choose to use a different shard to prevent Solana congestion on another app from affecting your app.\n\nThe shard id allows different applications to use different accounts for the same feed, thereby reducing the impact of solana congestion.\n\n## Fixed Address Pattern\n\nPrice feed accounts have a fixed address derived from the feed id and a shard id. Price feed accounts hold a sequence of prices for a specific price feed ID that always moves forward in time. These accounts have a fixed address that your program can depend on.\n\n## Getting Price Feed Account Addresses\n\nThe Pyth SDK provides methods to derive these addresses. For example, in TypeScript you can use methods like `getPriceFeedAccountAddress(shardId, feedId)` to obtain the account address for a specific feed and shard combination.\n\nThe search results don't contain detailed technical specifications about the exact PDA seed derivation algorithm or the specific seed structure used internally, but they confirm that the addresses are deterministically derived from these two parameters.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"eecaced5-6381-4fbb-9133-0bddb956e328"}
