{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017ALzS6yy4HhAnkwV4SfTjs","type":"tool_result","content":"# Solana Price Feed Accounts - Key Information\n\n## Account Type & Format\nPrice feed accounts on Solana use the **PriceUpdateV2** type. The documentation states: \"Add an `Account<'info, PriceUpdateV2>` field\" to access price data in Anchor-based programs.\n\n## Account Derivation\nTo obtain a price feed account address, use the `PythSolanaReceiver` class method:\n\n```typescript\nconst solUsdPriceFeedAccount = pythSolanaReceiver\n  .getPriceFeedAccountAddress(0, SOL_PRICE_FEED_ID)\n  .toBase58();\n```\n\nThe formula uses **shard_id** (0 in this example) and the **price feed ID** as inputs. There are \"up to 2^16 different accounts for any given price feed id.\"\n\n## Push vs. Pull Feeds\nBoth integration paths use identical account types from the on-chain perspective. The difference lies in maintenance: \"Push feeds\" receive sponsored updates from the Pyth Data Association, while pull feeds require explicit updates via transaction submission.\n\n## Account Ownership\nAccounts must be \"owned by the Pyth Pull Oracle program.\" Using Anchor's `Account<'info, PriceUpdateV2>` automatically validates ownership.\n\n## BTC/USD Feed Reference\nThe documentation references BTC/USD with this feed ID: `0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43`\n\n## Program Address\nThe specific Pyth program address isn't explicitly detailed in the provided content, though account validation is handled automatically by the SDK."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"91549083-ad0c-4d2e-ac63-384fe9869297"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0176BKuAyQrTs6u8CYy2XjMq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"pyth getPriceFeedAccountAddress typescript solana BTC USD shard 0 address derivation\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/use-real-time-data/pull-integration/solana\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Pyth for Price Feeds on Solana | Quicknode Guides\",\"url\":\"https://www.quicknode.com/guides/solana-development/3rd-party-integrations/pyth-price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@pythnetwork/pyth-solana-receiver\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-crosschain/target_chains/solana/sdk/js/pyth_solana_receiver at main · pyth-network/pyth-crosschain\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-crosschain/tree/main/target_chains/solana/sdk/js/pyth_solana_receiver\"},{\"title\":\"Price Feeds | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/price-feeds\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-sdk-solana 0.10.6 - Docs.rs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.rs/crate/pyth-sdk-solana/latest\"},{\"title\":\"Pyth: How to Use Real-Time Data in Solana Programs | Developers | Eclipse Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.eclipse.xyz/developers/tutorials-and-guides/developer-guides/pyth-how-to-use-real-time-data-in-solana-programs\"},{\"title\":\"on Solana | Pyth Developer Hub\",\"url\":\"https://docs.pyth.network/price-feeds/core/push-feeds/solana\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyth-network/pyth-client-js: Javascript API for on-chain pyth account structure\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-client-js\"},{\"title\":\"pyth-crosschain/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk/src/price_update.rs at main · pyth-network/pyth-crosschain\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyth-network/pyth-crosschain/blob/main/target_chains/solana/pyth_solana_receiver_sdk/src/price_update.rs\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about `getPriceFeedAccountAddress` in TypeScript for Solana Pyth:\n\n## Overview\n\nThe address of the price feed accounts can be derived automatically from the feed id and the shard id using `getPriceFeedAccountAddress`.\n\n## Basic Usage\n\nThe method is called like: `pythSolanaReceiver.getPriceFeedAccountAddress(0, SOL_PRICE_FEED_ID).toBase58()`, where the first parameter is the shard ID.\n\n## Shard ID Explanation\n\nThere are up to 2^16 different accounts for any given price feed id, and the shard id (0 in the example) indicates which of these accounts you would like to use.\n\nPrice feed accounts have a fixed address derived from the feed id and a shard id, and the shard id allows different applications to use different accounts for the same feed, thereby reducing the impact of solana congestion.\n\n## Changing the Shard\n\nThe example uses a shard id of 1, and changing the shard id to a different value will give you a different account address.\n\n## Sponsored Feeds\n\nThe Pyth Data Association sponsors price updates for a subset of commonly used price feeds on shard 0.\n\nFor BTC/USD specifically, you would use the BTC/USD price feed ID in place of `SOL_PRICE_FEED_ID` in the example above.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"4c69e0fd-83b9-4cd7-9801-bbe3557d2279"}
