{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W9ybNvuXR3zgvDKEUQe4bH","type":"tool_result","content":"# Address.ts File Content Analysis\n\nBased on the GitHub repository page you've provided, here's the complete file content for `address.ts`:\n\n## File Overview\nThe file is located at `target_chains/solana/sdk/js/pyth_solana_receiver/src/address.ts` and contains 69 lines (62 lines of code).\n\n## Program ID Constants\n\n```typescript\nexport const DEFAULT_RECEIVER_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  \"rec5EKMGg6MxZYaMdyBfgwp4d5rB9T1VQH5pJv5LtFJ\",\n);\n\nexport const DEFAULT_WORMHOLE_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  \"HDwcJBJXjL9FpJ7UBsYBtaDjsBUhuLCUYoz3zr8SWWaQ\",\n);\n\nexport const DEFAULT_PUSH_ORACLE_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  \"pythWSnswVUd12oZpeFP8e9CVaEqJg25g1Vtc2biRsT\",\n);\n```\n\n## Exported Functions\n\n**Four functions are exported:**\n\n1. `getGuardianSetPda()` - \"Returns the address of a guardian set account from the Wormhole program\"\n   - Seeds: `[\"GuardianSet\", guardianSetIndexBuf]`\n\n2. `getRandomTreasuryId()` - Returns random treasury ID (0-255)\n\n3. `getTreasuryPda()` - \"Returns the address of a treasury account from the Pyth Solana Receiver program\"\n   - Seeds: `[\"treasury\", [treasuryId]]`\n\n4. `getConfigPda()` - \"Returns the address of the config account from the Pyth Solana Receiver program\"\n   - Seeds: `[\"config\"]`\n\n**Note:** The file does not contain `getPriceFeedAccountAddress` or `getPriceFeedAccountForProgram` functions."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"657c8359-589c-47b0-aa56-2bb921b26840"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011WnMNjbkarsgyKRjqQ6uzL","type":"tool_result","content":"# getPriceFeedAccountAddress Method Analysis\n\n## Method Location\nThe `getPriceFeedAccountAddress` method is found in the `PythSolanaReceiver` class at lines 721-730.\n\n## Code Snippet\n```typescript\ngetPriceFeedAccountAddress(\n  shardId: number,\n  priceFeedId: Buffer | string,\n): PublicKey {\n  return getPriceFeedAccountForProgram(\n    shardId,\n    priceFeedId,\n    this.pushOracle.programId,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## PDA Derivation Details\n\n**Program ID Used:** `this.pushOracle.programId` (the Pyth Push Oracle program ID)\n\n**Seeds Construction** (from `getPriceFeedAccountForProgram` function, lines 752-773):\n1. **Shard Buffer**: A 2-byte little-endian encoded shard ID\n2. **Price Feed ID**: A 32-byte buffer representation of the price feed ID\n\n**Derivation Formula:**\n```typescript\nPublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n  [shardBuffer, priceFeedId],\n  pushOracleProgramId ?? DEFAULT_PUSH_ORACLE_PROGRAM_ID,\n)[0]\n```\n\nThe method converts string-based price feed IDs to buffers and validates that the feed ID is exactly 32 bytes long before deriving the PDA using Solana's standard `findProgramAddressSync` function."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"a7f87665-13ee-4265-a343-764750396e18"}
