{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CFqCsMk5HT66LRdTHk9TcQ","type":"tool_result","content":"# Program ID and Ownership Analysis\n\nBased on the `price_update.rs` file provided, here are my findings:\n\n## Owner Program ID\n**Not explicitly defined in this file.** The file contains struct definitions and implementation logic, but no `declare_id!` macro or program ID constant is present.\n\n## Account Attribute\nThe `PriceUpdateV2` and `TwapUpdate` structs use the `#[account]` attribute:\n\n```rust\n#[account]\n#[derive(BorshSchema)]\npub struct PriceUpdateV2 { ... }\n```\n\nThis Anchor macro indicates these are **program-owned accounts**, but the specific owner program must be defined elsewhere—likely in the main program file (probably `lib.rs` or `program.rs` in the same SDK).\n\n## Implication\nSince this is in `pyth_solana_receiver_sdk`, these accounts are owned by the **Pyth Receiver program**. The actual `declare_id!()` would be in the receiver program's main crate, not in this SDK support library.\n\nTo confirm ownership, check the receiver program's `lib.rs` for the `declare_id!` macro containing the program's public key."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011rr1yfgNLixmd4MBJw5da9","session_id":"846c05db-31a6-42c7-8cfa-8e6a53a70110","uuid":"dfaf5063-62bc-485d-83f5-c711a5462fe8"}
