e `Full` variant offsets listed above.\n\n### Actual price calculation\n`actual_price = price * 10^exponent`. For BTC/USD, exponent is -8, so a `price` of `7466237331000` means `$74,662.37`.\n\n## 3. Program IDs\n\n| Program | Address | Role |\n|---------|---------|------|\n| Pyth Push Oracle | `pythWSnswVUd12oZpeFP8e9CVaEqJg25g1Vtc2biRsT` | PDA derivation for push feed accounts |\n| Pyth Solana Receiver | `rec5EKMGg6MxZYaMdyBfgwp4d5rB9T1VQH5pJv5LtFJ` | Account owner; processes price updates |\n\nBoth are the same on mainnet and devnet.\n\n## 4. Compatibility with Existing Codebase\n\nThe existing `pyth.rs` parser in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/pyth.rs` is **correct and compatible** with the live devnet push oracle accounts:\n- It skips 8-byte discriminator (correct)\n- It deserializes `PriceUpdateV2Inner` via Borsh with the correct field order: `write_authority`, `verification_level`, `price_message`, `posted_slot`\n- The `PriceFeedMessage` struct matches: `feed_id`, `price`, `conf`, `exponent`, `publish_time`, `prev_publish_time`, `ema_price`, `ema_conf`\n- The `VerificationLevel` enum matches: `Partial { num_signatures: u8 }` and `Full`\n- The feed ID in the test file (`e62df6c8...415b43`) is the correct BTC/USD feed ID\n\nThe mock builder in the test file (`closecall.ts` line 49-106) builds a 133-byte buffer using the `Full` variant, which is correct for testing push oracle behavior.\n\n**One consideration**: The current on-chain program does not check account ownership (it uses `AccountInfo` with a `/// CHECK` comment). For production, you should verify the account owner is `rec5EKMGg6MxZYaMdyBfgwp4d5rB9T1VQH5pJv5LtFJ`.\n\n## 5. Feed ID Reference\n\nThe BTC/USD Pyth feed ID is: `0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43`\n\nThis is the same across all chains (Solana, EVM, etc.) -- it identifies the price feed, not the on-chain account."}],"totalDurationMs":496859,"totalTokens":70218,"totalToo